msgid "NARRATIVE_ABRAHAM_AND_SARAH_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_ABRAHAM_CALLED_TEXT"
msgstr "God called Abram to leave his homeland:\n\n'Go to the land I will show you,\nand I will make you a great nation.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_ASCENSION_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_BINDING_OF_ISAAC_DESC"
msgstr "Abraham's ultimate test of faith"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BINDING_OF_ISAAC_MAIN"
msgstr "God tested Abraham:\n'Take your son Isaac and offer him as a sacrifice.'\n\nAbraham obeyed, but God provided a ram instead."

msgid "NARRATIVE_BINDING_OF_ISAAC_NAME"
msgstr "The Binding of Isaac"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BIRTHRIGHT_SOLD_MAIN"
msgstr "Esau sold his birthright to Jacob\nfor a bowl of stew.\n\nA moment's hunger cost him everything."

msgid "NARRATIVE_BROTHERS_ARRIVE_EGYPT_DESC"
msgstr "Reunion and reconciliation"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BROTHERS_ARRIVE_EGYPT_MAIN"
msgstr "Famine drove Joseph's brothers to Egypt,\nseeking food.\n\nThey didn't recognize the brother they sold."

msgid "NARRATIVE_BROTHERS_ARRIVE_EGYPT_NAME"
msgstr "Brothers Arrive in Egypt"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BURNING_BUSH_DESC"
msgstr "God calls Moses"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BURNING_BUSH_MAIN"
msgstr "God spoke to Moses from a bush\nthat burned but was not consumed:\n\n'I will send you to Pharaoh.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BURNING_BUSH_NAME"
msgstr "The Burning Bush"

msgid "NARRATIVE_BURNING_BUSH_TEXT"
msgstr "The angel of the LORD appeared to him in flames of fire from within a bush. Moses saw that though the bush was on fire it did not burn up."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CAINS_DESCENDANTS_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_CAIN_AND_ABEL_MAIN"
msgstr "Abel's offering was accepted,\nbut Cain's was not.\n\nJealousy led to tragedy."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CALL_OF_ABRAHAM_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_CALL_OF_THE_FIRST_DISCIPLES_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY1_DESC"
msgstr "God creates light"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY1_NAME"
msgstr "The First Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY1_TEXT"
msgstr "In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. Now the earth was formless and empty, darkness was over the surface of the deep, and the Spirit of God was hovering over the waters. And God said, 'Let there be light,' and there was light."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY2_DESC"
msgstr "God separates the waters"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY2_NAME"
msgstr "The Second Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY2_TEXT"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let there be a vault between the waters to separate water from water.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY3_DESC"
msgstr "God creates land and vegetation"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY3_NAME"
msgstr "The Third Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY3_TEXT"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let the water under the sky be gathered to one place, and let dry ground appear.' And it was so. Then God said, 'Let the land produce vegetation.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY4_DESC"
msgstr "God creates the sun, moon, and stars"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY4_NAME"
msgstr "The Fourth Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY4_TEXT"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let there be lights in the vault of the sky to separate the day from the night, and let them serve as signs to mark sacred times, and days and years.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY5_DESC"
msgstr "God creates sea creatures and birds"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY5_NAME"
msgstr "The Fifth Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY5_TEXT"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let the water teem with living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the vault of the sky.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY6_DESC"
msgstr "God creates animals and humanity"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY6_NAME"
msgstr "The Sixth Day"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY6_TEXT"
msgstr "Then God said, 'Let us make mankind in our image, in our likeness.' So God created mankind in his own image, male and female he created them."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_1_DARKNESS"
msgstr "The earth was formless and empty,\nand darkness covered the deep waters..."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_1_LIGHT"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let there be light,'\nand there was light."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_2_INTRO"
msgstr "And God said, 'Let there be a vault between the waters to separate water from water.'"

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_3_MAIN"
msgstr "God said, 'Let the waters be gathered together,\nand let dry land appear.'\n\nAnd God saw that it was good."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_4_MAIN"
msgstr "God created two great lights—\nthe greater light to rule the day,\nand the lesser light to rule the night."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_5_MAIN"
msgstr "God created the great sea creatures\nand every living thing that moves in the waters,\nand every winged bird."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_6A_MAIN"
msgstr "God made the beasts of the earth,\nthe livestock, and everything that creeps on the ground."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_6B_MAIN"
msgstr "God created mankind in His own image,\nmale and female He created them.\n\nAnd it was very good."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_6_MAIN"
msgstr ""

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_DAY_7_MAIN"
msgstr "On the seventh day God finished His work,\nand He rested.\n\nGod blessed the seventh day and made it holy."

msgid "NARRATIVE_CREATION_INTRO_INTRO"
msgstr "In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth..."

